{"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"PIN code input is a UI element that allows to capture short, fixed-length numeric codes, typically for authentication or confirmation purposes,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"such as a four, six or eight-digit personal identification number (PIN)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"PIN code input is presented as a series of individual input fields or boxes, each representing a single digit, to enhance readability and encourage accurate input,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"while supporting smooth keyboard navigation and secured input masking if needed."}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSPinCodeInput","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/oudspincodeinput"]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@"},{"kind":"attribute","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","text":"MainActor"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSPinCodeInput"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"mentions":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Controls"],"kind":"mentions"},{"content":[{"anchor":"Layouts","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Layouts"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The component can be rendered as two different layouts:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"outlined"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" layout: A minimalist input with a transparent background and a visible stroke outlining the field."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This style may be interesting for contexts other than form pages, e.g. when inputs need to feel lightweight and unobtrusive,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in a header (search field), or in a selection\/filtering feature in a product catalog","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"not outlined","type":"text"}]},{"text":" (default): An input with a subtle background fill and visible bottom border, creating a softer and more contained look.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Best suited for dense layouts or to enhance visibility.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The component provides 3 layouts for the input: 4 boxes, 6 boxes or 8 boxes."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A helper text can be used to support text to convey additional information about the input field, such as how it will be used.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It should ideally only take up a single line, though may wrap to multiple lines if required, and be either persistently visible or visible only on focus.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Error status","anchor":"Error-status","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The Error status indicates that the user input does not meet validation rules or expected formatting.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It provides immediate visual feedback, typically through a red border, error icon, and a clear, accessible error message positioned below the input (mandatory).","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This state helps users quickly identify and correct mistakes by explaining what went wrong and, when possible, how to fix it.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The input remains editable, encouraging users to revise their input without starting over.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The error state must be triggered by an explicit validation (submission, API response), and not in real time with each keystroke.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This can occur either because the entered code does not match the expected code, because the user entered an expired or already used code,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"or finally if the maximum number of attempts has been exceeded.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Specific-design-guidelines","text":"Specific design guidelines"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In the context of a PIN code input, in addition to the input’s “Error” UI rendering, it is essential to also include an “Alert” component","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(also in its “Error” status) in the interface.","type":"text"}]},{"level":2,"text":"Particular cases","anchor":"Particular-cases","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSPinCodeInput","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" component supports autofill feature of values like OTP code."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For example if the user receives a message with inside a code the system can extract, the keyboard can suggest to the user to fill it."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If the digits fits the component, it will be filled."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If the digits are longer, they will be truncated."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If the digits are shorter, they will be filled, letting other fields empty."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The copy\/paste feature is also available and has the same behavior.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"text":"Technical considerations","anchor":"Technical-considerations","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For some cases, on phones screens or with 8 boxes in iPhone, you may need to use a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ScrollView"},{"type":"text","text":" to embed the component and let user move it."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["ScrollView(.horizontal) {","    OUDSPinCodeInput($value,","                     length: .eight,","                     helperText: \"Enter your secret code sent to your phone\")","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note also the exposed "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"value"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Binding"},{"type":"text","text":" will be updated when all digits are written."}]}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"text":"Accessibility considerations","anchor":"Accessibility-considerations","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The content of the fields is vocalized by Voice Over; the placeholders (defined in "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSPinCodeInput\/obfuscationCharacter","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSPinCodeInput\/placeholderCharacter","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":")"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"are not vocalized to let users know what they wrote."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The component gets only numeric values, not letters or symbols, only numbers."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Depending on the component configuration, autofocus can still be used when the component appears, and focus is moved to the next field as digits are entered."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For example if Voice Over is enavled, the autoficus is disabled."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The component and its digit fields are vocalized with internal wording."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When using the error status, provide a clear, concise error message explaining what went wrong and, when possible, how to fix it"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(for example: "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"“The code you entered is invalid. Try again.”"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":")."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use helper text to communicate additional guidance (for example: "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"“Check the 6‑digit code sent by SMS”","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":"), and keep this text short so it remains easy to vocalize"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and understand."}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Code-samples","text":"Code samples","level":2},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["    \/\/ The value with the code","    @State private var pinCode: String = \"\"","","    \/\/ By default, the PIN code input displays only 6 boxes","    OUDSPinCodeInput($pinCode)","","    \/\/ It can have also up 4 or 8 boxes, with an helper text","    OUDSPinCodeInput($pinCode, length: .eight, helperText: \"Enter your 8 secret digits\")","","    \/\/ The component can be used in error contexts","    OUDSPinCodeInput($pinCode, length: .six, status: .error(message: \"The OTP code you entered is not correct\"))"]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Design-documentation","text":"Design documentation","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"https:\/\/r.orange.fr\/r\/S-ouds-doc-pin-code-input","type":"reference","isActive":true}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Themes-rendering","text":"Themes rendering","level":2},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Orange","text":"Orange","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"iden